'Phenothiazine' is an organic compound that occurs in various antipsychotic and
antihistaminic drugs. It has the formula
S(C 6H 4) 2NH. This yellow tricyclic compound is
soluble in acetic acid, benzene, and ether. The compound is related to the thiazine-
class of heterocyclic compounds. Derivatives of the parent compound find wide
use as drugs.
